.TH EXCLI 1 "2026-07-12" "excalidraw-tui" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
excli \- open a .excalidraw file in the real Excalidraw, autosaving to the file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B excli
.RB [ \-\-tui ]
.I file.excalidraw
.br
.B excli
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B excli
opens a drawing in the genuine Excalidraw web app and saves your edits back to
.I file.excalidraw
automatically. The terminal acts as the launcher and a small autosave server;
the drawing itself opens in your browser.
.PP
If
.I file.excalidraw
does not exist yet, a blank canvas is started and the file is created on the
first save. Edits autosave roughly 500ms after you stop drawing.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-tui
Render the app inside this terminal via Carbonyl (Chromium in a terminal)
instead of opening a browser. Needs
.B npm install
first for the Carbonyl binary. It paints at terminal\-cell resolution \(em
blocky, best kept for SSH or headless boxes with no browser.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage and exit.
.SH MODES
In the default browser mode this terminal stays running as the autosave server:
leave it open while you edit and press
.B Ctrl\-C
when you are done. In
.B \-\-tui
mode, quitting Carbonyl ends the session.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I file.excalidraw
The drawing being edited. Holds the elements you draw.
.TP
.I ~/.config/excalidraw\-tui/config.json
Global config shared across all drawings: UI preferences (theme, canvas
background, zen/view mode, grid, snap) and your imported libraries. Global
preferences override whatever a drawing was saved with, so settings like dark
mode persist across reloads. Honors
.BR XDG_CONFIG_HOME .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the global config file. Defaults to
.IR ~/.config .
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Python 3, a browser, and internet access (Excalidraw and React load from the
esm.sh CDN). The
.B \-\-tui
mode additionally needs the Carbonyl binary via
.BR "npm install" ,
on macOS arm64 or Linux.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Open a drawing in the browser:
.B excli diagram.excalidraw
.TP
Start a new drawing (created on first save):
.B excli new-sketch.excalidraw
.TP
Render inside the terminal over SSH:
.B excli \-\-tui diagram.excalidraw
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Help was requested, or the session ended normally.
.TP
.B 1
Bad usage, or the autosave server failed to start.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project docs in
.IR PRODUCT.md .
Excalidraw: https://excalidraw.com
.br
Carbonyl: https://github.com/fathyb/carbonyl
